deck: Lucky Silva is Good Silva's brother. He can transform into a pink foxman with two tails.
description:
History

Lucky was living with his sister, Good Silva, and their parents in Detroit when a band of supervillains attacked their neighborhood. When their house was hit by a blast from Firebrand, Lucky was injured by the debris. Lucky was in the hospital for a while but let himself out the same night Dick Snerd was dropped at the hospital by the Great Lakes Avengers. Tracking his sister to GLA HQ, Lucky told her they were going to leave Detroit to avoid any trouble with Snerd once he gets out of the hospital. They were on the road but when Good got word that Big Bertha was in trouble, she left him at a gas station.

deck: Employee at Ferrari & Hindel Associates.
description:
History

Amy is employed by Ferrari and Hindel Associates as Connie Ferrari's assistant. Amy can usually be seen following behind Connie carrying her boss's briefcase and, sometimes, handling her phone calls. Whenever Connie needs a form handed out, Amy is there to reach into the brief and pull it out, such as when they offered full Avengers membership to Flatman and explained temporary membership to Good Boy. Amy handles Connie's appointments' scheduling and canceling as Connie needs, even Connie's dates. Amy is loyal to Connie even though her boss can be abrasive and comes off as having a perpetual bad mood. Amy has recently taken up online dating, using mobile apps targeted towards dating superheroes. She got the idea from her boss who was doing the same and Amy apparently had a good time with Gambit.

deck: A news reporter, one of many who reported on the Tanker Incident.
description:
Origin

Karen Hojo is a news reporter for Action News 10. She was present and reporting live when the Sons of Liberty, a terrorist group, seized control of the Big Shell, an offshore plant construction designed to help clean and deal with the environmental issues caused by a Tanker incident nearby. Hojo would report the events as they happened, including the involvement of supposed terrorist leader Solid Snake, the presence of Dead Cell, and several of Russian Colonel Sergei Gurlukovich's men, also terrorists, led by his daughter Olga Gurlukovich.

Creation

Karen Hojo is a fictional character created for the IDW Metal Gear Solid comic book series. She is created by writer Alex Garner and artist Ashley Wood. The Metal Gear Solid franchise is created by Konami, and creators such as Hideo Kojima and Yoji Shinkawa.

Powers and Abilities

Karen Hojo is an average human, with a fitness level consistent with a woman her age and size, with no additional abilities or powers. She possess experience in live news reporting.
name: Karen Hojo

deck: An extremely efficient and deadly sniper, assassin and soldier, Quiet has been an enemy and ally to the Diamond Dogs and their leader Big Boss.
description:
Origin

Quiet is mysterious sniper who operated in various locations in the world, but notably Afghanistan and the AngolaZaire border. Much of her past is unknown, however at one point she was an assassin operating for XOF, a covert strike force that existed to support FOX. During her service for XOF, Quiet would be sent to assassinate a high profile target, Big Boss, after he was reported to awake from a coma in Cyprus. However Big Boss's awakening was especially significant event, that created a flurry of commotion, with many parties attempting to act upon Big Boss, whether assassination, protection, or information gathering. During the chaos of the night, Quiet would attempt to assassinate Big Boss, but her attempts would be thwarted, with Big Boss and a fellow hospital patient managing to set Quiet on fire, struggling she would fall out a window from a great height.

Quiet would later appear operating in the Soviet-occupied Kabul Province area, as a sniper terrorizing Russian soldiers. Encountering Big Boss again, a long distance sniper battle would play out.

Creation

Quiet is a fictional character created by Hideo Kojima and Yoji Shinkawa, designed for the Metal Gear Solid franchise. She would first appear in the video game Metal Gear Solid V: The Phantom Pain released in 2015. She is voiced, modeled after and motion captured by Dutch model Stefanie Joosten.

Character Evolution

Quiet was introduced in the highly anticipated Metal Gear Solid V story, Metal Gear itself already a popular franchise with various video games, book adaptations, and comic books. One of the main characters of that story, she is the games main heroine, and features as an important subplot. Rather then existing as either an antagonist villain or good guy character, Quiet blurs between ally and mystery, her first few appearances attempting to kill the player character then later being recruitable with her own character and story development. Of note, Quiet is true to name, considered mute. The character also notably has many supernatural abilities and powers.

The character was the subject of some controversy due to the characters visual design. The character would go on to have some mixed reception upon the games release, many complimenting the characters writing, motivations, depth and mystery but still some criticism of the characters sexualization and attire.

Powers and Abilities

Pre-Parasite treatment, Quiet was a skilled and deadly assassin and soldier, who operated under XOF. Post-Parasite treatment, Quiet would develop powerful abilities, very similar to the various Skulls Parasites Unit. Superhuman speed, superhuman durability, superhuman agility, reflexes, and an ability to cloak in stealth, and exceptional eyesight and aim.

Physical Characteristics

  • Height: 5'6"
  • Weight:
  • Eyes: Green
  • Hair: Brown

Other Media

Metal Gear Solid V (2015)

Quiet appears in the fifth installment of the popular hit action game franchise, Metal Gear Solid V released n 2015. Based on the visual likeness and voice acted by Stephanie Joosten.
name: Quiet

deck: A data analyst who has personal connections to Raiden, Colonel Campbell and Solid Snake.
description:
Origin

Rosemary worked as data analyst for the USA military, as well as working as a spy for the Patriots. One of her missions was to infiltrate the life of an important asset to the Patriots, an individual known as Jack, codename Raiden. Rose was to endear herself to Raiden and start a relationship. She tailored herself to his general preferences and her initiation and task succeeded, with the two growing close and intimate. However during this time Rosemary began to have sincere feelings and was put in a difficult position.

When the Sons of Liberty terrorist group, supposedly lead by Solid Snake (in fact Solidus Snake) laid assault to and seized the Big Shell offshore environmental facility, both Raiden and Rosemary to get involved with the operation tasked to address the terrorists. Raiden would receive assistance from one Iroquois Pliskin (Solid Snake) as well as Hal Emmerich (Otacon) and Emma Emmerich.

Creation

Rosemary is a fictional character created for the Metal Gear Solid franchise. She would first appear in the video game Metal Gear Solid 2: Sons of Liberty released in 2001. Her character much like many of Metal Gear Solid's was primary created by Hideo Kojima and Yoji Shinkawa. Rose would appear in the IDW comic book series that adapted the Metal Gear Solid 2: Sons of Liberty story.

This series was written by writer Alex Garner and with art by artist Ashley Wood. The Metal Gear Solid franchise is created by Konami, and creators such as Hideo Kojima and Yoji Shinkawa.

Powers and Abilities

Rosemary possesses no significant powers or abilities, and has the physical abilities of a woman her size and age, who is healthy and in shape. She is a trained spy and data analyst.
name: Rosemary

deck: The younger sister of Hal Emmerich.
description:
Origin

Emma Emmerich is the younger step sister of Hal Emmerich. Both are incredibly intelligent and pursued careers in science and technology. Both share a father in Huey Emmerich. Emma pursued a career in AI technology. When they were both younger, an incident occurred in which Emma's mother, seduced her step son, Hal. This sordid affair would depress an already troubled Huey Emmerich who would commit suicide in the family swimming poor. He would also unintentionally drag a young Emma into the pool with him, and although she would survive, she would be severely traumatized by the event. Hal would also carry a guilt complex as Emma had been calling out for his help, but he hadn't heard her pleas. The brother and sister would become distant in years to come after the incident as well.

Later on in her life Emma would be involved in developing the AI for Arsenal Gear. After the Sons of Liberty terrorist group, supposedly lead by Solid Snake (in fact Solidus Snake) she would be kept as a prisoner. However eventually she would be rescued by Raiden, Iroquois Pliskin and her very own brother Hal Emmerich. Unfortunately in a showdown with Dead Cell member Vamp , Emma would be fatally wounded. She would have enough time to help Raiden, Snake and Otacon save the day, with her knowledge of advanced AI. She would also make amends and share a final warm moment with her big brother.

Creation

Emma Emmerich is a fictional character created for the Metal Gear Solid franchise. She would first appear in the video game Metal Gear Solid 2: Sons of Liberty released in 2001. Her character much like many of Metal Gear Solid's was primary created by Hideo Kojima and Yoji Shinkawa. Emma Emmerich would appear in the IDW comic book series that adapted the Metal Gear Solid 2: Sons of Liberty story.

This series was written by writer Alex Garner and with art by artist Ashley Wood. The Metal Gear Solid franchise is created by Konami, and creators such as Hideo Kojima and Yoji Shinkawa.

Powers and Abilities

Emma Emmerich is physically average human, with a fitness level slightly below consistent a woman her age and size, with no additional abilities or powers. She does however possess a very high and keen intellect, and competence in science. She specializes in AI research and developed important programs that helped rewrite Arsenal Gear.
name: Emma Emmerich
